content.description: A short crack route.  Climb a narrow crack up to a birch tree.
content.protection: Toprope with small cams and nuts.
content.location: Find a small overhang about ten feet off the ground.      Follow the crack up and slightly left.

content.description: A major crack on the inside of the chimney on the right wall.
Climb up the talus block staying right of trees, move up and left to a small seam.
content.protection: Nuts, cams and webbing for the toprope.
content.location: Find a chimney formed by a large block.  Just left of that is a pointed talus stone.

content.description: Climbs a shallow crack up to a ramp.
content.protection: Cams and webbing for the toprope.
content.location: About twenty feet to the right of the major corner.    Find the shallow crack.

content.description: From ledge on 16 step right and straight up the over hang. Stick the sloper and top out. Crux is finding the sloper and pulling up.
content.protection: TR can be done from the setup of 16 but best set up climber right of 16 Trad up 16 and one place ment in the overhang. Watch for loose rock.

content.description: Climbs the major right facing corner, lots of fun.  A few tough moves at the end.
content.protection: Webbing for trees and boulders, cams.
content.location: The face on the right facing corner.

content.description: A fun route, follows a thin crack system on the face just before the corner.  Moves up past a small roof at the top.
content.protection: Webbing and cams for the toprope setup.
content.location: Just left of the major right facing corner.  There is prominent boulder on the edge of the buttress, the climb is just below that boulder.

content.description: This is more of a variation to #15 than a route.  Find a junky crack system about ten feet off the ground and head up and then join #15.
content.protection: Top rope with nuts, cams and webbing.

content.description: Another good route.  Up a left leaning crack, traverse right into a v-groove and then up
content.location: Find a small left facing corner with a left leaning crack.  Setup is about right of #16.

content.description: A fun route, start at a left-leaning crack and head up through a pocketed face.  Continue up a roof using a hand crack.
content.protection: cams and nuts.  Setup is at the right end of a line of junipers.

content.description: A dirty/mossy route, not really worth the time.  A crack heads up the right side of the alcove, at the overhang you can go left or right.
content.protection: Cams and nuts to set up the toprope.
content.location: Find a dirty alcove with some downed trees to the right of #10.

content.description: A good route following a thin seam up and left.
content.location: About six feet to the left of #9.

content.description: More moderate routes than the West face.
